  "prompt": "What country catches the most lobsters?",
  "response": "As of the most recent data, the United States is one of the largest lobster-catching countries in the world, with the majority of its lobster harvest coming from the state of Maine. The American lobster (Homarus americanus) is the primary species caught in the U.S. and Canada.\n\nCanada is also a significant player in the lobster industry, particularly in the Atlantic provinces such as Nova Scotia, New Brunswick, and Prince Edward Island. Canadian lobsters are of the same species as those caught in the U.S.\n\nWhen it comes to volume and value, these two countries are often the top producers. However, other countries, such as Australia, New Zealand, and South Africa, also have notable lobster fisheries for different species like the Southern Rock lobster or the Cape lobster.\n\nFor the most up-to-date statistics, you would need to refer to global fisheries reports from organizations such as the Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO) of the United Nations or national fisheries departments. These reports can provide the latest information on which country is leading in lobster catches.",
